Is she– No.

406
00:16:08.217 --> 00:16:09.718  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:69.06% 
No?

407
00:16:08.217 --> 00:16:09.718  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:84.23% 
She’s gone.
She’s gone.

408
00:16:09.802 --> 00:16:11.720  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Lily! Lily! Lily! Lily!

409
00:16:11.804 --> 00:16:13.931  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
- No, the dress!
- [ Alarm Beeping ]

410
00:16:14.015 --> 00:16:15.057  position:85.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:75.93% 
Lily?

411
00:16:14.015 --> 00:16:15.057  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Lily?

412
00:16:15.141 --> 00:16:17.059  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:84.33% 
Wait, wait,
wait, wait!

413
00:16:17.977 --> 00:16:19.645  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
I can’t run
in these shoes!

414
00:16:19.729 --> 00:16:22.731  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I bet you wish
you had boy shoes now, huh?
Lily?

415
00:16:22.815 --> 00:16:26.276  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:70.50% 
[ Breathing Heavily ]
Claire, stop!

416
00:16:22.815 --> 00:16:26.276  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
What?

417
00:16:26.360 --> 00:16:28.070  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:75.93% 
Look!

418
00:16:26.360 --> 00:16:28.070  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
Oh, my God.

419
00:16:30.072 --> 00:16:32.992  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Okay, run, run.
Come on. Come on!

420
00:16:36.704 --> 00:16:38.705  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
She looks so happy.

421
00:16:38.789 --> 00:16:41.625  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
She does.
Oh, she really does.

422
00:16:41.709 --> 00:16:43.836  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
They’re gonna kill us.

423
00:16:43.920 --> 00:16:45.879  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
What sort of princess?

424
00:16:45.963 --> 00:16:49.591  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
The kind
that dances with beasts
and won’t marry Gaston.

425
00:16:49.675 --> 00:16:50.676  position:80.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:75.93% 
Really?

426
00:16:49.675 --> 00:16:50.676  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
What?

427
00:16:50.760 --> 00:16:52.261  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>It’s the only dress</i>
<i>she likes.</i>

428
00:16:52.345 --> 00:16:54.680  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Lily wants to come
to the wedding as Belle.

429
00:16:54.764 --> 00:16:57.433  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Makes sense.
She went to Pepper’s seder
as Dora the Explorer.

430
00:16:59.227 --> 00:17:01.854  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
- It’s fine.
- Are you sure?

431
00:17:01.938 --> 00:17:04.690  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>Yes. Yes.</i>
<i>As long as she’s happy.</i>

432
00:17:04.774 --> 00:17:08.277  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
A gay wedding is hardly
the place to stop someone
from being who they want to be.

433
00:17:08.361 --> 00:17:09.862  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Beeps ]

434
00:17:09.946 --> 00:17:12.948  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
- They said it’s fine.
- Yay! I’m finally happy!

435
00:17:13.032 --> 00:17:15.909  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:70.50% 
Mmm!
[ Laughs ]

436
00:17:13.032 --> 00:17:15.909  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
What?

437
00:17:15.993 --> 00:17:18.579  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
I saw you twirl.

438
00:17:15.993 --> 00:17:18.579  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
Oh, I did not.

439
00:17:18.663 --> 00:17:22.374  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
Yes, you did.
Such a pretty girl.

440
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:24.960  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Shut up.
<i>You’re</i> a girl.

441
00:17:25.044 --> 00:17:26.712  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
How about
that daughter of ours?

442
00:17:26.796 --> 00:17:29.214  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:70.50% 
She marches to the beat
of her own drum, huh?

443
00:17:26.796 --> 00:17:29.214  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
Yeah. Exactly.

444
00:17:29.298 --> 00:17:32.843  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
So why are we so concerned
what two nerdy teenagers
think of us?

445
00:17:32.927 --> 00:17:35.888  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Isn’t the true mark
of intelligence being able
to admit what you don’t know?

446
00:17:35.972 --> 00:17:37.347  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:75.93% 
Shh. Here comes Manny.

447
00:17:35.972 --> 00:17:37.347  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.66% 
Did he hear me?

448
00:17:37.431 --> 00:17:38.473  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
I don’t think so.

449
00:17:37.431 --> 00:17:38.473  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Hey, guys.

450
00:17:38.557 --> 00:17:40.767  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:69.06% 
Nothin’.

451
00:17:38.557 --> 00:17:40.767  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.23% 
Hey, what are you
doing out here?

452
00:17:40.851 --> 00:17:42.978  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
You guys invited us
so we could spend the day
together.

453
00:17:43.062 --> 00:17:46.231  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
It felt wrong that you two
are out here and I was in there
all alone with Alex.

454
00:17:46.315 --> 00:17:49.109  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
- Couldn’t keep up, could ya?
- She knows everything.
She made a docent cry.

455
00:17:49.193 --> 00:17:51.236  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:70.50% 
It’s okay.
We’re faking it too.

456
00:17:49.193 --> 00:17:51.236  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Well, duh.

457
00:17:51.320 --> 00:17:53.238  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:70.50% 
[ Alex ]
There you guys are.

458
00:17:51.320 --> 00:17:53.238  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
Nothin’.

459
00:17:53.322 --> 00:17:56.658  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
Uh, we were just
headed back in.

460
00:17:53.322 --> 00:17:56.658  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.66% 
Yeah, I’m getting a second wind.

461
00:17:56.742 --> 00:17:58.243  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, no, no, no.
That’s okay.

462
00:17:58.327 --> 00:18:00.329  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
- What do you say we go
check out some food trucks?
- Really?

463
00:18:00.413 --> 00:18:02.915  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I’ll go back in
if you guys want,
but I’m actually really hungry.

464
00:18:02.999 --> 00:18:04.625  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
- [ Manny ]
Yeah. Whatever you want.
- Whatever you need.

465
00:18:04.709 --> 00:18:06.502  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
Thanks, guys.

466
00:18:07.753 --> 00:18:10.255  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
If I’m being honest,
I had to get out of there.

467
00:18:10.339 --> 00:18:13.091  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
I was exhausted from having
to dumb it down all day.

468
00:18:13.175 --> 00:18:14.843  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Really? The neck?

469
00:18:14.927 --> 00:18:17.804  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
Yeah, a kiss on the neck
opens all kinds of doors.

470
00:18:17.888 --> 00:18:19.849  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Last one.

471
00:18:22.393 --> 00:18:25.187  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
Great job, champ.
Who said you can’t
build anything?

472
00:18:25.271 --> 00:18:27.648  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
My dad, the police, a doctor.

473
00:18:27.732 --> 00:18:29.775  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
You got a gift.
Trust me. Take shop.

474
00:18:29.859 --> 00:18:31.777  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:89.67% 
I think I’m gonna.

475
00:18:31.861 --> 00:18:34.363  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Hey, how’d you get to know
so much about everything?

476
00:18:34.447 --> 00:18:37.532  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
From my dad, mostly.
He taught me how to use a drill,
change a tire,

477
00:18:37.616 --> 00:18:40.452  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
fake an injury
when a buddy asks you
to help him move.

478
00:18:40.536 --> 00:18:42.204  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Everything a man needs
to get by.

479
00:18:42.288 --> 00:18:44.206  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
I’m just glad I have someone
to pass it on to.

480
00:18:44.290 --> 00:18:46.583  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
- You’ve got Manny.
- Mmm.

481
00:18:46.667 --> 00:18:49.419  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Manny came to me
kind of fully cooked.

482
00:18:49.503 --> 00:18:51.463  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
And I was an idiot
with Mitchell,

483
00:18:51.547 --> 00:18:54.466  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
and by the time this guy
gets old enough, who knows
how much I’ll remember?

484
00:18:54.550 --> 00:18:57.636  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
These are my prime
wisdom-giving years.

485
00:18:57.720 --> 00:18:59.346  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
You got any more
questions, Luke?

486
00:18:59.430 --> 00:19:01.515  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
Just one–
Can I have a sip?

487
00:19:01.599 --> 00:19:04.685  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
The beer? Sure.
What the hell.

488
00:19:01.599 --> 00:19:04.685  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.66% 
Awesome. My first drink of beer.

489
00:19:04.769 --> 00:19:08.855  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
I remember the day
I gave Mitchell
his first taste of beer.

490
00:19:08.939 --> 00:19:13.361  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
He winced and carried on
like someone was digging
a bullet out of his leg.

491
00:19:14.779 --> 00:19:17.322  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
I couldn’t take that moment
away from Phil.

492
00:19:17.406 --> 00:19:19.074  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:79.00% 
Hang on.
Wait a second.
Let me see that.

493
00:19:19.158 --> 00:19:22.077  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Sniffs ]
No, this beer’s skunked.

494
00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:25.372  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
It’s no good.
Damn fridge must be
on the fritz again.

495
00:19:25.456 --> 00:19:27.332  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Aw, man. Really?

496
00:19:27.416 --> 00:19:30.502  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
Sorry, buddy.
It’s probably time to call
your dad anyway, right?

497
00:19:30.586 --> 00:19:33.088  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:69.06% 
Okay.

498
00:19:30.586 --> 00:19:33.088  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.23% 
Wait a second. I want
to give you something.

499
00:19:33.172 --> 00:19:35.465  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:75.93% 
But those are yours.

500
00:19:33.172 --> 00:19:35.465  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:89.66% 
What’s a grandfather for...

501
00:19:35.549 --> 00:19:37.592  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:79.00% 
if he can’t give
his grandson
a couple of tools?

502
00:19:37.676 --> 00:19:40.638  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:75.93% 
Thanks, Grandpa.

503
00:19:37.676 --> 00:19:40.638  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Good job.

504
00:19:42.223 --> 00:19:45.684  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Joe. I know you’re all
about the boobs right now,

505
00:19:45.768 --> 00:19:49.605  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
but trust me– the neck.

506
00:19:51.774 --> 00:19:53.608  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Slowly ]
Don’t let go!

507
00:19:53.692 --> 00:19:56.445  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Slowly ]
Don’t worry, George Clooney!
I won’t!

508
00:19:56.529 --> 00:19:58.030  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.67% 
You’re too handsome!

509
00:19:58.114 --> 00:20:01.366  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Watch out
for incoming space junk!

510
00:20:01.450 --> 00:20:03.160  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
From where?

511
00:20:03.244 --> 00:20:05.245  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Your zipper’s down.

512
00:20:05.329 --> 00:20:07.289  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
[ Normal Voice ]
Oh, is it?

513
00:20:05.329 --> 00:20:07.289  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.66% 
Yeah, it is. Just–

514
00:20:07.373 --> 00:20:10.292  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:69.06% 
What’s Andy doing here?

515
00:20:07.373 --> 00:20:10.292  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.23% 
They’re making a video
for his girlfriend.

516
00:20:10.376 --> 00:20:12.127  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Yeah? What’s it called,
<i>Dorks in Space?</i>

517
00:20:12.211 --> 00:20:15.464  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, it was actually sweet.
It’s weird.

518
00:20:15.548 --> 00:20:17.215  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
There’s something about him.
You know what I mean?

519
00:20:17.299 --> 00:20:19.593  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Yeah, he’s just like Dad.

520
00:20:19.677 --> 00:20:22.054  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.67% 
Ew. Ew, ew!

521
00:20:22.138 --> 00:20:23.889  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
In space, no one
can hear you scream.

522
00:20:23.973 --> 00:20:24.973  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
What?

523
00:20:25.057 --> 00:20:28.185  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
In space, no one
can hear you scream!

524
00:20:28.269 --> 00:20:30.604  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:75.93% 
I can’t hear you!

525
00:20:28.269 --> 00:20:30.604  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
In spa–

526
00:20:30.688 --> 00:20:33.398  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:70.50% 
Oh, I just got it.
That’s good. That’s good.

527
00:20:30.688 --> 00:20:33.398  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Thank you.

528
00:20:33.482 --> 00:20:35.109  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Andy ]
That’s awesome.

529
00:20:38.154 --> 00:20:40.155  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
There’s no denying
it is original,

530
00:20:40.239 --> 00:20:42.240  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:79.00% 
but you can see
the influence
of Pollock.

531
00:20:42.324 --> 00:20:44.868  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:5.00% 
While the pattern seems
haphazard and random,

532
00:20:44.952 --> 00:20:47.746  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:5.00% 
it belies a purposefulness,
an intentionality.

533
00:20:47.830 --> 00:20:52.084  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
You know, I think what I’m
responding to is the clashing
juxtaposition of color,

534
00:20:52.168 --> 00:20:54.753  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
the bright yellow against
the dark background.

535
00:20:54.837 --> 00:20:58.965  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
It’s like a ray of sunshine
in an otherwise bleak world.

536
00:20:59.049 --> 00:21:01.426  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:5.00% 
If I may take
a contrary position–

537
00:21:01.510 --> 00:21:04.763  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:5.00% 
I think it speaks to
the absurdity and folly
of human endeavor.

538
00:21:04.847 --> 00:21:05.931  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
Mmm.

539
00:21:06.015 --> 00:21:08.517  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:5.00% 
Like our futile struggle
for perfection.

540
00:21:08.601 --> 00:21:11.603  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
I get it.
I got mustard on my shirt.
Get over it.

541
00:21:11.687 --> 00:21:14.982  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I know we’re joking, but all
kidding aside, it really does
remind me of Kandinsky’s–

